If you want to keep the power and keep it grounded

Treat it as open performance shaping, not a hidden trick:

* Name the frame: “Let’s run a quick experiment to get into a rhythm.”
* Keep one cue: fewer moving parts = more consistency.
* Measure it: try it over multiple rounds/people so you’re not relying on a single highlight.
* Debrief out loud: “Here’s what likely helped—focus, rhythm, confidence.”
    (This keeps trust and turns it into something they can reuse.)

